{\rtf1\ansi \deff0{\fonttbl{\f8\fswiss Arial;}}\margl720\margr2160\pgnstart30\sectd\pgnrestart\pgnstarts30\footery1080{\header \pard\plain\ql MYARC ADVANCED BASIC\par }{\footer \pard\plain\ql \chpgn     VERSION 4.0  DDI SOFTWARE  \par }\pard \plain\f8\fs20 CLEAR -Subprogram\tab \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab CLEAR\par \par \par \par \par Format\par CALL CLEAR\par \par Cross Reference\par DCOLOR, DELSPRITE\par \par Description\par The CLEAR subprogram erases the screen.\par \par CLEAR places a space character (ASCII code 32) in every screen position.\par \par The CLEAR subprogram has no effect on sprites. Use the DELSPRITE subprogram to remove sprites.\par \par Programs\par \par When the following program is run, the screen is cleared before the PRINT statements are performed.\par \par 100 CALL CLEAR\par 110 PRINT "HELLO THERE!"\par 120 PRINT "HOW ARE YOU?"\par RUN\par --screen clears\par HELLO THERE!\par HOW ARE YOU?\par \par If the space character (ASCII code 32) has been redefined by the CALL CHAR subprogram, the screen is filled with the new character when CALL CLEAR is performed.\par \par 100 CALL CHAR(32,"0103070F1F3F7FFF")\par 110 CALL CLEAR\par 120 GOTO 120\par RUN\par --Screen is filled with *\par (Press CLEAR to stop the program.)\par \par The following program first fills and then clears the entire screen.\par \par 100 CALL GRAPHICS(1,2)\par 110 CALL HCHAR(1,2,72,768)\par 120 FOR DELAY=1 TO 500::NEXT DELAY\par 130 CALL CLEAR\par 140 GOTO 140\par RUN\par (Press CLEAR to stop the Program.)\par }
